features: SPARKLING CLEAN WITHOUT HARSH CHEMICALS: Powered by plant-derived enzymes, Clean People's Dishwasher Detergent Pods naturally cut through grease & stuck-on food stains to leave dishes sparking with zero residue, streaks, or other mineral build-up. Safe, simple, effective, Clean People's products free from ethoxylates and cruelty-free.

CONVENIENT & EASY TO USE: Safe for use on glassware, porcelain, stainless steel, pots & pans, baby bottles and more! Simply rinse dishes prior to loading (works with built-in, portable & drawer styles), add pod and let Clean People do the hard work!

GOOD FOR YOU, GOOD FOR THE ENVIRONMENT: Our eco friendly dishwasher pods are powered by natural, plant based enzymes; That means no phosphates, parabens, phthalates, chlorine bleach, artificial dyes, petroleum, ammonia!

POWERFUL YET GENTLE: Our low sudsing dish detergent contains active enzymes to dissolve food, grease & grime without harsh chemicals or any rinse aids. Works on all stain types and is tested effective with both hard and soft water
WHATS INCLUDED: 120 count bag of Dishwasher Detergent Pods. Free of harsh synthetic fragrances, dyes, and other harmful chemicals such as ethoxylates

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 15, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I always look for the most environmentally friendly and economical choices, but sometimes they don't work as well as we'd like them too. I am also very sensitive to fragrance so I don't like the liquid pods. The previous powder pods I bought before these were lousy, leaving all the dishes feeling like they weren't rinsed thoroughly enough and sometimes the dishes weren't even clean. So I was afraid to try more powder pods. But these work much better! Dishes are clean and don't need an extra rinse. Happy to have found a good solution. Less waste, no fragrance, works great!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I feel safer using these!
reviews.reviewText: I was using cascade for a while until my kids kept getting sick and saying their milk tastes weird. I checked everything and it came down to the dish pods. I think they were leaving a film on their plastic cups. I started using these and we have had no more problems! There isn't much of a strong smell and I feel so much more safe using them. I am in fact about to order more! I just reuse my old cascade tub and carefully place them into it. They clean just as good or better. I use my cascade tabs for my mop water now until they are gone. This product gave me peace of mind washing dishes and I won't ever go back to regular pods again. Thank you!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Cleans well, waterspots
reviews.reviewText: These pods work great and price is comparable to the more common brands. If waterspots bother you, you will probably want to get a rinse agent as well for plastics and teflon.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great dishwasher pods, no residue
reviews.reviewText: I really like these dishwasher pods. We used to use cascade I believe, which always left a residue on our dishes. This does not do that at all. The dishes come out just as clean as they did with the Cascade pods.They do clump together a little in the bag like others have said but it is not hard at all to simply pull them apart. I have never had any rip open.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars These work as well for me as Finish Powerballs, and far less toxic!
reviews.reviewText: I have used Finish Powerballs for years because they were top-rated by Consumer Reports, and they got our dishes and glasses cleaner than anything else. But recently, I have been switching all our cleaning products to less toxic varieties. This Clean People product is fabulous, though pricey. I will continue to use it for sure. The only thing I am not crazy about is the smell. They say it's lemon fresh, but the pods smells rather plastic-like to me right out of the bag. Fortunately, very little smell is left once the dishes are clean and dry.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Works great! Already using the second order!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024

reviews.reviewText: I wanted to love this as I have switched to this brand for laundry detergent. It’s absolutely terrible. I have used four times and every time I have to rewash the dishes because it leaves a sticky film on everything.
